OpenAI just dropped Atlas, a Chromium-based ChatGPT browser built for “vibe lifing”. While Microsoft launched Copilot Mode in Edge along with Mico, a new Clippy-style assistant. Linus and Luke mock both for being near-identical AI browsers that claim to “respect privacy” and roast Microsoft for not just bringing actual Clippy back.
